call_variants.py does this, step by step:

Query NCBI for all Ebola genomes per species (using species scientific name to avoid contamination)
Fetch genomes in batches from NCBI
Extract metadata: accession, strain/isolate, host, collection date, country, genome length, completeness
Extract proteins:
First tries NCBI CDS annotations
If no CDS and genome is full (≥15kb), extracts ORFs using reference coordinates
Align each protein to the matching reference protein
Call variants: substitutions, insertions, deletions, stop gains/losses, frameshifts
Store only metadata and variant calls in PostgreSQL — no sequences are saved
Create per-species/per-gene views for fast querying


